transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Yeah, hello.

Speaker 2: My name is Patrick, and I was trying to understand why you guys sent me a double order.

Speaker 1: Let me see what's going on here. What was your last name, Mr. Patrick?

Speaker 2: Patrick.

Speaker 1: What was your first name?

Speaker 2: Nathaniel.

Speaker 1: Just a sec here.

Speaker 2: Is your 31 Short C or 37 Long B?

Speaker 1: Give me just a sec.

Speaker 2: And you're at 3790 39th Avenue, Apartment 5?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, so I see what happened here.

Speaker 1: It looks like you guys set up on our VIP prescription after the first order to receive refills, Mr. Patrick.

Speaker 2: Well, I just did the one-time order.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay, okay.

Speaker 2: I can pause that service for you if you wanted to keep the account active,

Speaker 1: push the refill all the way to June, July, give you some time in between orders if you need it.

Speaker 2: No, I just wanted it as I needed it, so I'll do that then.

Speaker 1: So if I cancel it out completely, I won't be able to fill the prescription for you in the future, Mr. Patrick.

Speaker 2: That's why I was saying I could pause it until July, and you can call us any time before then if you do need it in the next six months.

Speaker 1: If not, you can always let us know as well.

Speaker 2: All right, do that then.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay.

Speaker 2: Yep, so that will be until July then, Mr. Patrick.

Speaker 1: Any time before then, give us a shout, and we can take care of you.

Speaker 2: Or if you need more time, you're traveling or whatever, just give us a call, and we can push it further as well, okay?

Speaker 1: All right, sir. Thank you.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you. Bye-bye now.
